The HAWKS in Mbombela, Mpumalanga, have launched a manhunt for Sifiso Innocent Mabuza (39). This in relations to an investigation for fraud and contravention of the tax administration Act. It is alleged that during 2018 and 2021, Mabuza was the director of a company that submitted fraudulent tax returns to South African Revenue Service and prejudiced it an amount of R28 million. ALSO READ: Earn R10K a month to play a car racing game! “The investigation team managed to trace Mabuza, who promised to hand himself over but never did,” Hawks spokeswoman Captain Dineo Lucy Sekgotodi said. A court has issued a warrant for his arrest, and Sekgotodi has urged anyone who knows his whereabouts to contact Lieutenant-Colonel Thabelo Takalani on 071 481 2848.